This module is built to work wit the House Proceedings Corpus (HPC), a highly structured 
corpus of complete congressional house proceedings that contains over 2,700 transcripts, 
tagged for part-of-speech (POS) using the Stanford POS tagger. The HPC is comprised of 
individual .JSON files to avoid data-corruption and easily importable into a MongoDB.  
It is available upon request.  The HPC has 181,648,994 tokens with a vocabulary of 314,031 
words. 

